Given a matroid $M\subseteq \bF_2^n\setminus \{0\}$ and an $(\eta,r,d)$-regular partition $f_1+f_2+f_3$ of $M$ with corresponding factor $\cB$, for any $\eps,\zeta>0$ define the $(\eps,\zeta)$-\emph{reduced matroid} $R=R_{\eps, \zeta}$ to be the subset of $\bF_2^n$ whose indicator function is constant on each atom $b$ of $\cB$ and equals $1$ on $b$ if and only if
\begin{enumerate}
    \item $\bE[|f_3(x)|^2\mid x\in b]\leq \eps^2$, and
    \item $\bE[f(x)\mid x\in b]\geq \zeta$.
\end{enumerate}

